# ── GearMedic / agent POST: one password, any text you like ───────────────────
# Same string here, in your host (e.g. Vercel) env, and in GearMedic as:
#   Authorization: Bearer <that same string>
# Pick something simple if you want, e.g. abs123  (fine for personal / test sites)
INGEST_PASSWORD=
# Older names still work if you already use them:
# AGENT_INGEST_SECRET=
# XALURA_INGEST_TOKEN=
# XALURA_AGENT_BEARER=

# (GearMedic / KV ingest — phaseout; ignore unless you still run that path.)
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=
# GET /api/ingest-health after deploy to verify KV + password are picked up

# Optional: until first approve/decline in Admin, POST may work without Bearer
# After that, Bearer (INGEST_PASSWORD) is required unless you set:
# AGENT_UPDATE_OPEN_INGEST=true
# Testing only — wrong password still inserts pending row:
# AGENT_UPDATE_ACCEPT_ANY=true

# ── Xalura agentic (xalura-agentic/) — Phases 1–7 (see docs/agentic-workflow-architecture-log.md) ──
# Docs: docs/agentic-workflow-architecture-log.md
#
# Minimum to turn on real LLM (Worker/Manager/Executive paths in pipelines):
# Paste your key from Google AI Studio — never commit real keys to the repo.
GEMINI_API_KEY=
# Optional model id (default in code: gemini-2.5-flash-lite):
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash-lite
# Optional resilience (Phase 6 — lib/gemini.ts):
AGENTIC_GEMINI_TIMEOUT_MS=60000
AGENTIC_GEMINI_RETRIES=3
#
# If GEMINI_API_KEY is empty, pipelines still run with stubs (Manager can APPROVE).
# Set the same vars on Cloudflare (Workers) for /api/agentic-health gemini_configured: true.
# Must be on the **deployed Worker** (OpenNext / wrangler name), not only “build” env in CI.
#
# Optional: shown in `/api/agentic-health` `deploy_fingerprint` when CI does not set a commit env var.
BUILD_REF=

# One-time debugging (no key values returned): set a random string here and on Cloudflare, then:
#   GET /api/agentic-health?debug=<that same string>
# Response may include `gemini_env_debug` (booleans + typeof binding + truncated errors). Remove token when done.
AGENTIC_HEALTH_DEBUG_TOKEN=
#
# Optional live Gemini proof (one generateContent; uses API quota — do not put on dumb uptime polls):
#   GET /api/agentic-health?gemini_ping=1   (also: true, yes)
# Optional timeout for that call only (default 20000 ms):
# AGENTIC_GEMINI_PING_TIMEOUT_MS=20000
#
# Admin AI dashboard: publishing cadence bar (ms). Default 7200000 = 2h wall-clock slots (display only).
# AGENTIC_DASHBOARD_PUBLISH_CYCLE_MS=7200000
#
# Cloudflare **cron** (see `wrangler.jsonc` + `cloudflare/custom-worker.ts`) — all use Bearer `AGENTIC_CRON_SECRET`:
# - **Hourly** `0 * * * *` → `POST /api/cron/agentic-incremental` — **incremental** article path: one vertical (round-robin) SEO (topic bank) → Publishing → optional site. 24 ticks/day, **1 h** apart. Serp refresh: `AGENTIC_TOPIC_BANK_MIN_SERP_INTERVAL_HOURS` (default 72h).
# - **Every 10 min** `*/10 * * * *` → `POST /api/cron/agentic-chief-sweep` — Chief trend snapshot (no Serp).
# - **Every 2h** `0 */2 * * *` → `POST /api/cron/agentic-publish` — **full** one-shot article publish + site (same as admin) at **0,2,4,…,22 UTC** — **12**/day, **120 min** between same-route fires.
# - **Every 3h** `0 */3 * * *` → `POST /api/cron/news-run` — full **News** pipeline in one request — **0,3,6,9,12,15,18,21 UTC** — **8**/day, **180 min** apart. **lcm(2,3)=6h**: at **0,6,12,18 UTC** both 2h and 3h triggers run (two HTTP calls).
#   Any cron string in `triggers` without a matching `else if` in `custom-worker.ts` still **defaults** to `agentic-publish`.
# Optional incremental tuning:
# AGENTIC_TOPIC_BANK_MIN_SERP_INTERVAL_HOURS=72
# Parallel topic lanes (hourly): default **1** = one topic, serial. Set **2–10** to run up to that many topics per tick (SEO → Publishing per lane; higher Gemini/email load).
# AGENTIC_INCREMENTAL_BATCH_SIZE=1
# Min topic-bank `final_score` for hourly picks (1–100). Default **80**. Only `unused` rows with a public `subcategory` and non-regulated `vertical_id` are eligible.
# AGENTIC_MIN_TOPIC_SCORE=80
# AGENTIC_INCREMENTAL_SEO_TASK=…   (override default SEO brief for hourly tick)
# AGENTIC_INCREMENTAL_PUBLISH_TASK=… (override default article brief)
# AGENTIC_INCREMENTAL_AUTO_SITE_PUBLISH=true|false — default follows `AGENTIC_AUTO_PUBLISH_TO_SITE` when unset.
#
# Staggered incremental (one step per HTTP call: SEO handoff → Publishing → site) — **Spread work across a 2h window** instead
# of running the full monolithic path every tick. Use `POST /api/cron/agentic-incremental-stagger` (same `Authorization: Bearer` as
# other crons) on e.g. a 10–15 minute schedule. Set `AGENTIC_INCREMENTAL_STAGGER=true` and keep `AGENTIC_INCREMENTAL_BATCH_SIZE=1`.
# Post-site compliance / founder email now **awaits** by default on the site step. To defer (faster JSON response; may not send in some Workers): `AGENTIC_INCREMENTAL_STAGGER_DEFER_OVERSIGHT=true` (replaces the old `AGENTIC_INCREMENTAL_STAGGER_AWAIT_OVERSIGHT=1` “opt-in to await” pattern).
# Needs writable `xalura-agentic/state/`. If stagger is on, **do not** also run `POST /api/cron/agentic-incremental` on the same
# cadence or the topic/vertical advance may **double** with the hourly incremental cron.
#
# Local: `npm run agentic:incremental-once` (uses `.env.local` like other smokes).
#
# ── Agentic News team (`/news`, `POST /api/cron/news-run` — same Bearer as other crons) ──
# Chief snapshot text: optional `NEWS_CRON_INTERVAL_HOURS` (default **3** — should match `wrangler.jsonc` + worker mapping).
# Pre-Production: SerpAPI `google_news` (no scraping raw Google HTML). Optional Firecrawl on result URLs.
# `npm run agentic:smoke-news` — network Serp only. `NEWS_SMOKE_FULL=1` runs full pipeline dry (no publish, no image) — needs GEMINI.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_NEWS_… — none; news uses same Supabase as articles + `news_items` / `news_run_events` tables.
# SERPAPI_API_KEY — required for Pre-Prod + checklist
# NEWS_SERP_TIMEZONE=UTC
# NEWS_PREPROD_MIN=20
# Optional 1–3: full pipeline restarts if Chief of Audit rejects (each restart = more Serp/Firecrawl; use 1 on strict CF Worker subrequest budgets).
# NEWS_MAX_AUDIT_RETRIES=2
# NEWS_SERP_QUERY_AI=artificial intelligence
# NEWS_SERP_QUERY_TECH=technology
# Extra Serp queries if you need more rows (defaults built-in: “artificial intelligence news”, “technology news today”):
# NEWS_SERP_QUERY_EXTRA=artificial intelligence news
# NEWS_SERP_QUERY_EXTRA2=technology news today
# NEWS_CHECKLIST_SERP_QUERY=AI news
# Optional: same bucket as article covers; uploads under `news/` path (`lib/newsCoverStorage.ts`).
# LEONARDO_API_KEY — Photographer step when `withImage: true` on cron

# Topic bank: default is `xalura-agentic/state/topic-bank.json` (needs writable disk). On read-only hosts (e.g. Cloudflare Workers), persist the bank in Supabase instead:
# AGENTIC_TOPIC_BANK_USE_SUPABASE=true
# Requires `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` + `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` and table `public.agentic_topic_bank` (see `supabase/schema.sql`). When true, reads prefer Supabase then fall back to disk; writes go to Supabase and still mirror to disk when writable.
# Admin org-chart names (`public.agentic_agent_names` + `loadAgentNamesResolved`) use the same service role. When the deploy filesystem is read-only (e.g. Cloudflare), saves from `/api/admin/agentic-names` go to this table; reads merge it over `config/agents.json`.
# Per-stage pipeline log (Worker / Manager / Executive) for Chief awareness — table `public.agentic_pipeline_stage_log` in the same `schema.sql`. Set true to turn off read/write (saves a round-trip; no rows then):
# AGENTIC_PIPELINE_LOG_DISABLE=false
# wrangler secret put AGENTIC_CRON_SECRET   (strong random; NOT the same as AGENTIC_RUN_TOKEN)
# Worker vars (dashboard → Settings → Variables, or wrangler vars):
# AGENTIC_CRON_BASE_URL=https://www.xaluratech.com   (origin only, no trailing slash; used by scheduled handler to self-fetch)
# If unset, scheduled handler falls back to AGENTIC_PUBLIC_BASE_URL then NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL.
# Optional override for the article brief each cron tick:
# AGENTIC_CRON_PUBLISH_TASK=Write a Markdown article about …
#
# POST /api/agentic/run — Bearer auth (run pipelines + optional Supabase publish):
# Prefer a dedicated secret (set on the Worker too):
# AGENTIC_RUN_TOKEN=
# If AGENTIC_RUN_TOKEN is unset, the same bearer as INGEST_PASSWORD is accepted.

# Per-SEO-topic research (keyword + subcategory): **SerpAPI** + **Firecrawl** on every SEO run with `useTopicBank` (unless `skipPhase7Fetch` on the request). Set to **1** to disable (saves API quota; not recommended in prod):
# AGENTIC_SEO_SKIP_TOPIC_SERP=0
#
# Phase 7 — HTTP clients in `xalura-agentic/lib/phase7Clients.ts` (health shows `phase7` flags):
# Pipelines: SEO Worker context pulls GSC top queries when OAuth + site URL are set; any department
# can pass JSON `referenceUrl` to POST /api/agentic/run for Firecrawl → Worker context. Topic-bank SEO also gets `phase7_topic_serp_*` from `seoTopicResearchContext.ts`.
# Marketing: after each approval, `GET …/profiles` (Zernio) — see `result.phase7.zernio`; if `AGENTIC_MARKETING_ZERNIO_POST`, also `result.phase7.marketingZernio` (rolling recent article + 35h default cooldown).
# Publishing: after a successful Supabase article upsert, optional `POST …/v1/posts` when enabled — see `publish.zernio` in run JSON.
# AGENTIC_AUTO_PUBLISH_TO_SITE=true — approved publishing runs upsert `articles` without sending publishToSite:true (send publishToSite:false to opt out; never combine with useHandoff).
# AGENTIC_ZERNIO_POST_ON_PUBLISH=true — after site publish, call Zernio (needs ZERNIO_API_KEY; targets queue, explicit JSON, or default all active accounts — see Zernio env block).
# AGENTIC_MARKETING_ZERNIO_POST=true — on Marketing approval, pick one random article published in the last **35h** (UTC rolling window; override with `AGENTIC_MARKETING_ZERNIO_ARTICLE_LOOKBACK_HOURS`) and POST to Zernio if the last such post was **≥35h** ago (override `AGENTIC_MARKETING_ZERNIO_COOLDOWN_HOURS`), tracked in `agentic_marketing_zernio_state`. Same Zernio env as on-publish; needs `GEMINI_API_KEY` + migration `20260428120000_agentic_marketing_zernio_state`.
# AGENTIC_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://www.your-domain.com — public https origin for Zernio links, emails, etc. (same as NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL; Workers: set this or NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL). Also read: AGENTIC_CRON_BASE_URL if you use it for cron.
# Zernio “where to post”: (1) `ZERNIO_QUEUED_FROM_PROFILE_ID` if set (queue). (2) Else non-empty `ZERNIO_POST_PLATFORMS_JSON`. (3) Else **default: GET /v1/accounts, every active connection** (no flag required). Set `ZERNIO_POST_ALL_ACTIVE_ACCOUNTS=false` only if you want to **forbid** that default and force queue or JSON.
# ZERNIO_POST_ALL_ACTIVE_ACCOUNTS= — leave blank or `true` / `1` for default all-active; use `false` / `0` / `no` to require explicit queue or JSON.
# ZERNIO_ACCOUNTS_PROFILE_ID= — optional; limits default “all accounts” to one Zernio profile (`?profileId=` on GET /v1/accounts).
# ZERNIO_QUEUED_FROM_PROFILE_ID= — profile _id from GET /v1/profiles (queue) when you prefer queue over instant multi-post.
# ZERNIO_POST_PLATFORMS_JSON= — e.g. [{"platform":"twitter","accountId":"<account _id>"}] to post only to listed accounts.
# Alerts (optional Resend): failures appended to `failed/operations-queue.json`; batched digest email (not per-failure):
# AGENTIC_OPS_ALERT_EMAIL=you@example.com
# AGENTIC_OPS_ALERT_INTERVAL_HOURS=12 — min hours between pipeline alert digests (default 12).
# After Chief enriches a 10-cycle audit file on disk:
# AGENTIC_CHIEF_DIGEST_EMAIL=you@example.com
# After each successful **site publish** (publishToSite), optional Chief cycle digest to that same inbox:
# AGENTIC_CHIEF_EMAIL_ON_PUBLISH=true
# **Add-on (does not change digest/compliance):** one inbox for **article + news publish outcomes** and what was logged (success, manager vs executive vs technical), including failed site upsert and non-approved publishing runs. Uses Chief memo + Resend `CHIEF_RESEND_FROM` / `RESEND_FROM` like the digest. Set to blank to disable.
# AGENTIC_CHIEF_PUBLISH_OUTCOME_REPORT_EMAIL=you@example.com
# Optional: send **facts only** (no extra Chief AI prose); default uses Gemini when `AGENTIC_CHIEF_OUTCOME_GEMINI` is not `false` or `0`.
# AGENTIC_CHIEF_OUTCOME_GEMINI=true
# Chief AI email tone + signature (Ryzen Qi): optional verified From for Resend:
# CHIEF_RESEND_FROM=Ryzen Qi <RyzenQi@xaluratech.com>
# Optional second publish-email From for the Chief of Audit news send:
# CHIEF_NEWS_AUDIT_RESEND_FROM=Richard Maybach <richardmaybach@xaluratech.com>
# Optional real Resend CC (comma-separated) — for **/articles** publish notes this is not applied; for **news** it is merged with desk CC below.
# CHIEF_EMAIL_CC=vp@xaluratech.com,compliance@xaluratech.com
# **News** post-publish digest: CC = CHIEF_EMAIL_CC + (CHIEF_NEWS_DESK_CC or HEAD_OF_NEWS_DIGEST_EMAIL + NEWS_AUDITOR_DIGEST_EMAIL) + always richardmaybach@xaluratech.com (deduped).
# CHIEF_NEWS_DESK_CC=headofnews@xaluratech.com,richardmaybach@xaluratech.com
# Optional top-of-body memo (display) for that news message only: CHIEF_NEWS_MEMO_TO=  CHIEF_NEWS_MEMO_FROM=richardmaybach@xaluratech.com  CHIEF_NEWS_MEMO_CC_LINE=
# Body “memo” line (display, default Chief mail): CHIEF_EMAIL_MEMO_TO=  CHIEF_EMAIL_MEMO_FROM=  CHIEF_EMAIL_MEMO_CC_LINE=  (defaults in lib/chiefEmailBranding.ts)
# HTML signature logo uses NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL (or AGENTIC_PUBLIC_BASE_URL) + /email/xalura-xt-logo.png
# Compliance / founder email after each successful site publish (admin, cron, API — same code path). No veto. Includes Compliance Officer memo (scored rubric D1–D7 + counsel-style posture), risk level, draft email with **display-only** Cc: Chief AI, Executives (not Resend cc:). **By default the route awaits** `executeFounderOversightPublishEmail` (Resend + Gemini + optional image) so email actually sends on Cloudflare; pass `awaitFounderOversight: false` at the call site only if you intentionally defer to background `waitUntil` (unreliable on some hosts):
# **Checklist — all must be true on the runtime that performs the publish** (Next.js vs Cloudflare Worker each has its own env):
# (1) AGENTIC_COMPLIANCE_ON_PUBLISH=true **or** AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_ON_PUBLISH=true
# (2) Inbox: AGENTIC_COMPLIANCE_EMAIL and/or AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_EMAIL and/or AGENTIC_CHIEF_DIGEST_EMAIL (fallback order)
# (3) RESEND_API_KEY (+ optional RESEND_FROM verified sender)
# (4) GEMINI_API_KEY (memo + analyst blocks; rubric is advisory, not legal advice)
# AGENTIC_COMPLIANCE_ON_PUBLISH=true
# AGENTIC_COMPLIANCE_EMAIL=you@example.com
# (Aliases — either on-flag or both can be set; email falls back in order:)
# AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_ON_PUBLISH=true
# AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_EMAIL=you@example.com
# (Blank compliance/founder email falls back to AGENTIC_CHIEF_DIGEST_EMAIL.)
# Optional hero image: flash-lite art brief → **Leonardo** (default when `LEONARDO_API_KEY` is set) or **Imagen** → **Supabase Storage** `article-covers` + `articles.cover_image_url`, and email attachment when compliance mail runs. Run the `article-covers` block in `supabase/schema.sql` (or Dashboard → Storage). On Cloudflare, `wrangler.jsonc` sets this to true by default; override in Dashboard if needed.
# AGENTIC_GRAPHIC_DESIGNER_ON_PUBLISH=true
# Optional strict mode: refuse the Supabase upsert unless a cover URL was produced (requires AGENTIC_GRAPHIC_DESIGNER_ON_PUBLISH=true and a working `article-covers` bucket):
# AGENTIC_REQUIRE_COVER_ON_PUBLISH=true
# Leonardo (photoreal; see `xalura-agentic/lib/leonardoGenerate.ts`):
# LEONARDO_API_KEY=
# Optional: `leonardo` | `imagen` — if unset, uses Leonardo when `LEONARDO_API_KEY` is set, else Imagen.
# AGENTIC_HERO_IMAGE_PROVIDER=leonardo
# PhotoReal v2: use a v2‑compatible base model (e.g. Leonardo Kino / Diffusion / Vision XL) or the API returns “Invalid model id”.
# If unset, code defaults to Kino XL. Override to another compatible id from Leonardo’s PhotoReal docs:
# LEONARDO_MODEL_ID=aa77f04e-3eec-4034-9c07-d0f619684628
# LEONARDO_WIDTH=1280
# LEONARDO_HEIGHT=720
# LEONARDO_PHOTO_REAL=true
# PhotoReal v1 can omit a model; v2 requires a compatible model (see `leonardoGenerate.ts` default or set LEONARDO_MODEL_ID):
# LEONARDO_PHOTO_REAL_VERSION=v2
# LEONARDO_PRESET_STYLE=PHOTOGRAPHY
# Imagen (fallback) model id (REST `:predict` — `xalura-agentic/lib/imagenGenerate.ts`):
# AGENTIC_IMAGE_MODEL=imagen-4.0-ultra-generate-001
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# Optional verified sender (default many accounts use for tests: onboarding@resend.dev):
# RESEND_FROM=onboarding@resend.dev
#
# Resend inbound → Chief + News (POST /api/webhooks/resend-chief-inbound):
# In Resend: enable Receiving, add webhooks `email.received`, copy each endpoint’s signing secret.
# Chief (or legacy single webhook) — try first at verify:
# RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# Optional second webhook (Head of News / Chief of Audit inbox) — same path; try second if first fails:
# RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET_2=
# Comma-separated From addresses allowed to get a Chief reply (required; empty = no replies):
# CHIEF_INBOUND_ALLOWED_SENDERS=you@example.com
# Optional: who may use “executive override” tone in Chief’s reply (if unset, all allowlisted senders are treated as executive):
# CHIEF_INBOUND_EXECUTIVE_SENDERS=you@example.com
# Optional: who may use ---CHIEF_COMMAND--- email blocks to run pipelines (if unset, same as CHIEF_INBOUND_ALLOWED_SENDERS):
# CHIEF_INBOUND_ACTIONS_SENDERS=you@example.com
# Optional: only process mail whose To includes this substring (e.g. chief@yourdomain.com):
# CHIEF_INBOUND_TO_FILTER=chief@
# Inbound Chief AI reply: max words (default ~2500, slightly higher when News context applies). `unlimited` = no clip.
# CHIEF_INBOUND_MAX_WORDS=2500
# Optional: skip persisting email threads in Supabase (inbound+outbound are not stored; Chief has no back-read from DB).
# CHIEF_EMAIL_THREAD_LOG_DISABLE=true
#
# Same webhook (`/api/webhooks/resend-chief-inbound`) — route by **To** address (substring match, case-insensitive):
# HEAD_OF_NEWS_INBOUND_TO=headofnews@     # e.g. Head of News inbox; checked before Chief
# CHIEF_OF_AUDIT_NEWS_INBOUND_TO=auditor@ # e.g. Chief of Audit (News) inbox; checked before Chief
# (CHIEF_INBOUND_TO_FILTER still limits which mail is processed; add Hon/Aud substrings to that filter or leave chief-only filter if you use separate receiving routes.)
# Optional: comma allowlist (defaults to CHIEF_INBOUND_ALLOWED_SENDERS if unset):
# NEWS_TEAM_INBOUND_ALLOWED_SENDERS=you@example.com
# From addresses (verified in Resend); fall back to CHIEF_RESEND_FROM / RESEND_FROM:
# HEAD_OF_NEWS_RESEND_FROM=headofnews@yourdomain.com
# CHIEF_OF_AUDIT_NEWS_RESEND_FROM=auditor@yourdomain.com
# Optional CC on News team Resend sends:
# NEWS_TEAM_EMAIL_CC=
# After a news article publishes — uses the **same** Chief post-publish path as /articles (`scheduleChiefPublishCycleEmail`):
# AGENTIC_CHIEF_EMAIL_ON_PUBLISH=true
# AGENTIC_CHIEF_DIGEST_EMAIL=you@example.com
# CHIEF_RESEND_FROM=chief@yourdomain.com
# CHIEF_NEWS_AUDIT_RESEND_FROM=richardmaybach@yourdomain.com
# News publish now sends two emails: one ops note + one audit note.
# (Optional; CHIEF_NEWS_ACTIVITY_EMAIL_ON_PUBLISH is no longer required for news — same flag as articles.)
# Optional: also send legacy separate Head of News + Chief of Audit digests (same as before):
# CHIEF_NEWS_LEGACY_NEWS_TEAM_EMAILS=true
# HEAD_OF_NEWS_EMAIL_ON_PUBLISH=true
# HEAD_OF_NEWS_DIGEST_EMAIL=you@example.com
# NEWS_AUDITOR_EMAIL_ON_PUBLISH=true
# NEWS_AUDITOR_DIGEST_EMAIL=you@example.com
#
# Optional — apply `supabase/migrations/20250424000000_chief_email_threads.sql` to the hosted DB from the CLI.
# In Supabase → Project Settings → Database, copy the connection string (URI, with password; URL-encode special chars in the password for use in a URL).
# Then: export SUPABASE_DB_URL='postgresql://...' && npm run db:apply-chief-email
# Email command example (run SEO with topic bank; add line: approve), see lib/chiefInboundCommandParse.ts
# FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=
# Optional override (default https://api.firecrawl.dev):
# FIRECRAWL_BASE_URL=
# ZERNIO_API_KEY=
# Optional API root (default https://zernio.com/api):
# ZERNIO_API_BASE=
# Topic bank “web search” uses **SerpAPI** (not Google Custom Search). Key: https://serpapi.com/manage-api-key
# SERPAPI_API_KEY=
# Optional engine id for SerpAPI (default: google): SERPAPI_ENGINE=google
# Smoke: npm run agentic:diagnose-serpapi
# POST /api/agentic/content/refresh-topic-bank — same Bearer as agentic run (forces new bank).
# Each refresh: **one Serp call** → ~20 ranked topics (all CONTENT_VERTICALS) + `xalura-agentic/state/seo-trend-logs.json`.
# POST /api/agentic/run JSON: `contentVerticalId` (e.g. `developer-tools-oss`) with `useTopicBank` (SEO) or publishing lane override.
# Each vertical id gets its **own** 10-cycle ladder + markdown under `xalura-agentic/logs/seo/lanes/{id}/` and `.../publishing/lanes/{id}/` (see `data/cycle-state.json` → `agentLanes`).

# Google Search Console — DIFFERENT product (analytics for YOUR site). Optional OAuth + site URL:
# GOOGLE_SC_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_SC_SECRET=
# GOOGLE_SC_REFRESH_TOKEN=
# GOOGLE_SC_SITE_URL=https://your-domain.com/

# Docs only — create admin in Supabase Auth
ADMIN_EMAIL=
ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# BEGINNER TABLE — Variable | What you actually type (not all are required)
# Copy NAME=value lines into `.env.local`. Cloudflare: wrangler secret put NAME for secrets.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# | Variable                      | What to put |
# |-------------------------------|-------------|
# | AGENTIC_RUN_TOKEN             | Any strong random string YOU make up. Used as Bearer token for POST /api/agentic/run. Leave blank to reuse INGEST_PASSWORD as Bearer instead. |
# | GEMINI_MODEL                  | Optional. Exact model id string (e.g. gemini-2.5-flash-lite). Blank = code default. |
# | AGENTIC_GEMINI_TIMEOUT_MS     | Optional. Number only, e.g. 60000 (milliseconds). Blank = default in code. |
# | AGENTIC_GEMINI_RETRIES        | Optional. Number only, e.g. 3. Blank = default. |
# | AGENTIC_GEMINI_PING_TIMEOUT_MS | Optional. For /api/agentic-health?gemini_ping=1 only. Blank = default. |
# | BUILD_REF                     | Optional. Short text like a git commit or deploy label. Blank is OK. |
# | SERPAPI_API_KEY               | Secret from serpapi.com dashboard (topic bank + SEO `useTopicBank`). |
# | SERPAPI_ENGINE                | Optional. SerpAPI `engine` param; default `google`. |
# | FIRECRAWL_API_KEY             | Secret from firecrawl.dev dashboard. |
# | FIRECRAWL_BASE_URL            | Usually LEAVE BLANK. Only set if Firecrawl gave you a custom API base (otherwise default is https://api.firecrawl.dev). |
# | GOOGLE_SC_CLIENT_ID           | OAuth “Client ID” string from Google Cloud (Search Console API access). Optional. |
# | GOOGLE_SC_SECRET              | OAuth “Client secret” from same client. Optional. |
# | GOOGLE_SC_REFRESH_TOKEN       | One long token from OAuth flow with offline access — not a URL. Optional. |
# | GOOGLE_SC_SITE_URL            | Your property URL exactly as in Search Console, e.g. https://example.com/ — not an API path. |
# | RESEND_API_KEY                | Secret from resend.com (starts with re_). |
# | RESEND_FROM                   | An email you’re allowed to send from in Resend (verified sender). Can be blank for dev default in code. |
# | RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET         | Svix signing secret for the Resend `email.received` webhook (Chief; verified first). |
# | RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET_2        | Optional second `email.received` webhook (news team; verified if the first secret fails). |
# | CHIEF_INBOUND_ALLOWED_SENDERS | Comma-separated sender emails that may email Chief and receive a reply. Required for inbound replies. |
# | CHIEF_INBOUND_EXECUTIVE_SENDERS | Optional. Comma-separated senders who get “executive override” behavior in Chief’s prompt. If blank, all allowlisted senders do. |
# | CHIEF_INBOUND_ACTIONS_SENDERS  | Optional. Comma-separated senders allowed to run `---CHIEF_COMMAND---` + `approve` actions. If blank, same as allowlist. |
# | CHIEF_INBOUND_TO_FILTER       | Optional substring; if set, webhook only runs when a To address contains it (e.g. chief@). |
# | CHIEF_INBOUND_MAX_WORDS      | Optional. Inbound reply word cap; default high in code. `unlimited` = no cap. |
# | AGENTIC_OPS_ALERT_EMAIL       | YOUR email for batched pipeline failure digests (not per-failure; see `AGENTIC_OPS_ALERT_INTERVAL_HOURS`). |
# | AGENTIC_OPS_ALERT_INTERVAL_HOURS | Hours between digest emails; default 12. |
# | AGENTIC_CHIEF_DIGEST_EMAIL     | YOUR email for optional Chief audit notifications. |
# | AGENTIC_CHIEF_EMAIL_ON_PUBLISH | true = email Chief digest after each successful article publish (needs digest email + Resend + Gemini for best text). |
# | AGENTIC_COMPLIANCE_ON_PUBLISH | true = email compliance report after each successful publish (same as founder oversight path). |
# | AGENTIC_COMPLIANCE_EMAIL | Inbox for that report; blank → AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_EMAIL → AGENTIC_CHIEF_DIGEST_EMAIL. |
# | AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_ON_PUBLISH | true = same email pipeline as compliance (either flag may be used). |
# | AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_EMAIL | Inbox when compliance email blank; else chief digest email. |
# | AGENTIC_GRAPHIC_DESIGNER_ON_PUBLISH | true = optional hero image (art brief from Gemini; render via Leonardo or Imagen). |
# | LEONARDO_API_KEY                | Leonardo.Ai API key; when set, hero images use photoreal path unless AGENTIC_HERO_IMAGE_PROVIDER=imagen. |
# | AGENTIC_HERO_IMAGE_PROVIDER     | Optional: leonardo | imagen. Unset = Leonardo if `LEONARDO_API_KEY` is set, else Imagen. |
# | AGENTIC_IMAGE_MODEL           | Imagen model id when using Imagen; default imagen-4.0-ultra-generate-001. |
# | ZERNIO_API_KEY                | Secret API key from Zernio. Optional. |
# | ZERNIO_API_BASE               | Almost always LEAVE BLANK. Only if Zernio gave a custom API root URL (otherwise code uses default host). |
# | AGENTIC_AUTO_PUBLISH_TO_SITE  | true = publishing + approved → Supabase upsert without publishToSite in JSON; false/blank = only when body has publishToSite:true. |
# | AGENTIC_ZERNIO_POST_ON_PUBLISH | true = after successful site publish, POST to Zernio (see Phase 7 Zernio: default all active accounts unless queue/JSON/opt-out). |
# | AGENTIC_MARKETING_ZERNIO_POST | true = on Marketing approval, one Zernio post from a random article in the lookback window; cooldown vs last post in `agentic_marketing_zernio_state` (defaults 35h; env overrides below). |
# | AGENTIC_MARKETING_ZERNIO_COOLDOWN_HOURS | Min hours between marketing Zernio posts; default 35. |
# | AGENTIC_MARKETING_ZERNIO_ARTICLE_LOOKBACK_HOURS | How far back to pick published articles; default 35. |
# | AGENTIC_PUBLIC_BASE_URL       | Canonical site URL for links in Zernio posts, e.g. https://xalura.com — prefer on Cloudflare Workers if NEXT_PUBLIC_* is build-only. |
# | AGENTIC_CRON_SECRET           | Strong random string. Bearer for POST /api/cron/agentic-publish and for the Worker scheduled self-fetch. wrangler secret put. |
# | AGENTIC_CRON_BASE_URL         | Public site origin only, e.g. https://www.xaluratech.com — Worker cron uses this to call /api/cron/agentic-publish. Plain var (not secret). |
# | AGENTIC_CRON_PUBLISH_TASK     | Optional. Overrides the publishing `task` string for each cron run (else same default as admin publish). |
# | ZERNIO_POST_ALL_ACTIVE_ACCOUNTS | blank/true = default: all active accounts; false/0 = require queue or `ZERNIO_POST_PLATFORMS_JSON`. |
# | ZERNIO_ACCOUNTS_PROFILE_ID   | Optional: filter default all-active list to one Zernio profile. |
# | ZERNIO_QUEUED_FROM_PROFILE_ID | If set, queue path (skips default all-active and explicit JSON). |
# | ZERNIO_POST_PLATFORMS_JSON    | If set and non-empty, explicit `publishNow` targets (skips default all-active). |
#
